  "label": "The Sealed Locker",
  "description": "A pitch-scented storage room set off The Iron-Straked Passage behind a low, iron-braced hatch, its tar-black planking bound with riveted straps to endure shock and sea-swell. Wall racks and chained cradles hold cask staves, coil-ropes, spare strakes, and caulking tins under stamped inventory tags, while a narrow deck-grate keeps goods above bilge damp. Jurisdiction plaques are bolted beside the threshold, and a waist-high line of salt-caked warding nails continues along the interior bulkhead as standard hazard protocol.",
